{"uid":"72017ef181f24b11","name":"test_watcher_production_profile_az_blocked","fullName":"tests.integration.ha_tests.test_stereo_mode#test_watcher_production_profile_az_blocked","historyId":"b4a3d198059bec95456819f0acabdbc8","time":{"start":1784858941194,"stop":1784859272131,"duration":330937},"description":"Test watcher with profile=production blocks on AZ co-location.\n\n    When all units are in the same availability zone (common on single-host\n    LXD deployments), a watcher with profile=production should enter\n    BlockedStatus because it shares an AZ with the PostgreSQL units.\n    This validates the AZ enforcement behavior.\n\n    If JUJU_AVAILABILITY_ZONE is not set (some CI environments), the watcher\n    should reach active status since no AZ co-location can be detected.\n\n    Since watcher-offer has limit: 1, we must remove the existing testing watcher\n    before deploying the production one, then restore it afterward.\n    ","descriptionHtml":"<p>Test watcher with profile=production blocks on AZ co-location.</p>\n<pre><code>When all units are in the same availability zone (common on single-host\nLXD deployments), a watcher with profile=production should enter\nBlockedStatus because it shares an AZ with the PostgreSQL units.\nThis validates the AZ enforcement behavior.\n\nIf JUJU_AVAILABILITY_ZONE is not set (some CI environments), the watcher\nshould reach active status since no AZ co-location can be detected.\n\nSince watcher-offer has limit: 1, we must remove the existing testing watcher\nbefore deploying the production one, then restore it afterward.\n</code></pre>\n","status":"passed","flaky":false,"newFailed":false,"newBroken":false,"newPassed":false,"retriesCount":1,"retriesStatusChange":true,"beforeStages":[{"name":"charm","time":{"start":1784856800230,"stop":1784856800231,"duration":1},"status":"passed","steps":[],"attachments":[],"parameters":[],"shouldDisplayMessage":false,"stepsCount":0,"attachmentsCount":0,"hasContent":false,"attachmentSt